    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1883-06-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1883-06-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="296"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d296">
                <head>No. 296.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">West</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Frelinghuysen</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-06-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 8, 1883</date>. (Received June
                        9.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to your note of the 19th ultimo,
                    and to previou s correspondence on the subject, I have the honor to inclose to
                    you extract <pb facs="0573" n="503" xml:id="pg_503"/> of a letter from the Hon.
                    E. Dewdney, lieutenant-governor of the Northwest Provinces, to the secretary of
                    the Governor-General, respecting the incursions of the Piegan Indians.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>L. S. SACKVILLE WEST.</signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure.—Extract.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Hon. <persName type="from">E. Dewdney</persName> to
                            Colonel <persName type="to">de Winton</persName>.</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-05-28">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">May</hi> 28, 1883</date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>Our Indians at Maple Creek are very slow to get off; they are now holding a
                        sun dance. Piepot has just promised to start in five days.</p>
                    <p>They have all left the Walsh neighborhood, being afraid of the South Piegans,
                        who are out in numerous small war parties trying to steal what few horses
                        our Indians have left. Colonel Ilges, of Fort Assinniboine, has just sent
                        word to our police that another war party is on its way to Walsh. Our
                        Indians have no ammunition, and are much afraid of the Piegans. There is not
                        much fear of our Indians crossing again.</p>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
        </body>
